BROKEN ARROW, Okla. (AP) â€” A 12-year-old boy has died after being struck by a hit-and-run driver while sledding in Broken Arrow.Police in the Tulsa suburb said the boy, whose name was not released, was sledding Thursday afternoon when he went into a city street and was struck.The boy was taken to a hospital where he later died, according to Police Officer Chris Walker.Walker said the driver did not stop after striking the child and has not been located.Walker said a second 12-year-old boy suffered minor injuries when he was also struck by a vehicle while sledding in a separate accident.The Tulsa area received about six inches of snow as a major winter storm moved through the area.Clearing skies were forecast Friday, although wind chill advisories for low temperatures continued in most of the state.